The paper discusses Neural Architecture Search (NAS), which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The experiments are conducted on image classification datasets (cs.CV), and the paper discusses the importance of the search space and the evaluation protocol (cs.DC). Finally, the paper proposes best practices for NAS, which is relevant to the broader machine learning community (cs.NE).
